[SECTION]
TITLE: Functional Feature Specifications

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: REQ-INDEX-001
STATUS: Draft
PRIORITY: Must
TITLE: Feature Requirements Index
STATEMENT: >>>
This index lists the per-feature functional requirement documents that specify the detailed behaviour of each Termicap sub-system. Each document uses UID-prefixed FUNC-XXX-NNN identifiers and follows the StrictDoc GRAMMAR block format defined in this index.

Feature documents:

  functional/xtversion.sdoc  (REQ-XTV)  — Active terminal identification via XTVERSION (CSI > q / DCS >| ... ST)
  functional/da1.sdoc        (REQ-DA1)  — DA1 Primary Device Attributes response parsing (CSI c / ESC [ ? Ps ; ... c)
  functional/decrpm.sdoc     (REQ-RPM)  — DECRPM private mode queries (CSI ? Ps $ p / CSI ? Ps ; Pm $ y)

Top-level requirement documents at this level:

  01-vision.sdoc             — Project vision, goals, and scope
  02-functional.sdoc         — High-level functional requirements summary (REQ-FUNC)
  03-non-functional.sdoc     — Non-functional requirements (performance, portability, SPARK provability)
  osc-query-infra.sdoc       — OSC/DCS/CSI probe session and sentinel-bounded query infrastructure
  bg-color-query.sdoc        — Background and foreground colour detection via OSC 10/11
  dark-light.sdoc            — Dark/light theme classification via BT.601 luminance (REQ-DKL)
  terminal-identification.sdoc — Passive terminal identification from environment variables
  terminal-dimensions.sdoc   — Terminal dimensions detection via TIOCGWINSZ
  unicode-support.sdoc       — Unicode support level detection
  color-downsampling.sdoc    — Colour downsampling from TrueColor to 256/16 colour palettes
  capability_record.sdoc     — Terminal_Capabilities aggregate record assembly
  func-override.sdoc         — NO_COLOR / FORCE_COLOR / programmatic override
  sigwinch.sdoc              — SIGWINCH handler for terminal resize notification
  kitty-keyboard.sdoc        — Kitty Keyboard Protocol detection (CSI ? u sentinel probe)
  mouse-protocol.sdoc        — Mouse Protocol Detection (DECRPM modes 1000/1002/1003/1006/1015/1016, GPM fallback)
<<<
COMMENT: >>>
This index document exists as a navigational aid and cross-reference hub for the full Termicap requirements corpus. StrictDoc discovers all .sdoc files in the docs/requirements/ directory tree automatically; this index does not need to enumerate every file for the tool to process them. Its value is human navigability: a reader opening the requirements directory can find this file first and use it to understand the scope and organisation of the specification before diving into individual feature documents.
<<<

